ce:section.ce:para:
Since the Gilmore–Akulichev model has a wide range of applicability (Mach number less than 

                           2.2

                     ) [33], it was used to simulate bubble dynamics in soft tissue. The Zener equation was used to model the viscoelastic tissue [34]. Note that previous studies of the inertial cavitation threshold mainly used the Keller–Miksis model [27,26,31,32]. However, the Keller–Miksis equation has some limitations and can be applied only for Mach numbers less than 1 [35]. Therefore, the Gilmore–Akulichev model is preferable for simulating the inertial cavitation threshold.
